theorem Topology.P1_iff_P2_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ Topology.P2 A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    -- From `P1` and the fact that `A` is closed we obtain `closure (interior A) = A`.
    have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = A :=
      closure_interior_eq_of_isClosed_and_P1 (A := A) hA_closed hP1
    -- Hence `A` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
      isOpen_of_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hEq
    -- For open sets, `P1` and `P2` are equivalent.
    have hEquiv := Topology.P1_iff_P2_of_isOpen (A := A) hOpen
    exact hEquiv.mp hP1
  · intro hP2
    exact Topology.P2_implies_P1 (A := A) hP2

theorem isOpen_of_closure_interior_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = A → IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  intro hA
  have : IsOpen (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := isOpen_interior
  simpa [hA] using this
